author: Aaron Howes
title: Caliroots & Nordic Brand CLEAN Are Releasing an Apparel Collaboration
text:
Visit the original post to see all 5 images from this gallery. 
Following up on its recent collaboration with Diemme , streetwear and sneaker retailer Caliroots is releasing a logo crewneck with Norwegian brand CLEAN.
The design was put together by Caliroots and CLEAN founder Christina Ledang whose logo crewnecks have been popular in Norway since she started the brand in 2012. The crewneck features the CLEAN logo embroidered on the front and comes in two colors — gray and pink .
Christina Ledang is a designer based in Oslo focusing mainly on womenswear. CLEAN stands for Christina Ledang Essentials Always Necessary; Ledang designs wardrobe essentials with the intention of making women feel comfortable and confident in their own skin.
The Caliroots x CLEAN logo crewneck will release online in both colorways on March 2 for €110.
